<br>
As she walked past the gathering of the male Gods, she turned once and grinned at each of them. She was the virgin Goddess, the temptress, much like Aphrodite only none had ever been able to conquer the favored daughter of Zeus. <br>
<br>
Her mother had been Zeus' first wife, Metis. She was the first and most wise, Athena was chosen to overthrow Zeus. It was decreed by the Fates. Perhaps that was why Zeus favored her so greatly. Athena had no grudges against her Father. She loved him dearly, but if the time came when he had been killed, or had chosen to go on his own, she would glady fill her Father's shoes. . . or should she say throne.<br>
<br>
Her gold glimmered in the light as she nodded a greeting to Maia. She then kneeled down to face her half-brother. As she looked into his eyes she saw purity and a soul of loyalty. She smiled seeing this. &quot;You shall indeed be one among few of honor on Olympus young Hermes.&quot; <br>
<br>
She too knew what he was going through. Although she was the first conceived child of Zeus, she was not born until the others had been. Most of them were children of Hera, or mortals, or other Nymphs and Driads, but she was the daughter of a Goddess, and at first her brothers and sisters hated her for it. <br>
<br>
&quot;In time they shall soften their hearts to you Hermes,&quot; She spoke to the boy, &quot;But do not fear them, for I have heard that Hera herself has sworn to keep you out of harms reach. The sister Furies do not wish you harm either.&quot; She smiled up at the sisters, especially Tisiphone. &quot;They are not here to bring harm, but justice to those that do wrong. You have done nothing wrong here little brother.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled to the child and blinked those hazel eyes that shook Olympus on command.<br>
<br>
