<br>
&quot;Lets go for a ride!&quot; Apollo said, still himself a child in many ways. Even in appearance he was a child, a mere boy of 17. His hair brustled along as he ran from the temple, his little brother clinging to his head. He liked forming the bond his Hermes, he was bound and determined to be the boys favorite brother, and Apollo rarely did not get what he wanted. Apollo placed Hermes on the ground, watching him interact with his world.<br>
<br>
&quot;I will make this one great...&quot; he said to himself, planning to be a big brother/ father type to Hermes, for the Fates know that Zeus would rarely be around for him. Apollo laughed and raised his hands to his lips, whistling, calling forth to him his wolf pup Ashley. Ashley was a blondish blue eyed wolf pup. He was great with children and a good friend.<br>
<br>
&quot;You like dogs?&quot; Apollo asked, bending down to greet Ashley, who greeted him with a slobbery lick. Ashley soon moved over to Hermes and started to sniff him. He happily yipped and started to run about.<br>
